  "DOI": "10.1021/acs.chemmater.1c00456",
  "summary": "The paper provides a comprehensive overview of how molecular architecture controls selectivity in area-selective atomic layer deposition (AS-ALD). It explains the mechanistic roles of surface-blocking inhibitors and ALD precursors, discusses structure–reactivity relationships (functional groups, steric bulk, binding motifs), and outlines design rules that enable long nucleation delays on non-growth areas while sustaining high growth rates on target surfaces. The authors combine experimental results and theoretical insights to guide the rational design of next-generation inhibitors and precursors for self-aligned nanoscale fabrication."
